There are several suspicious processes with sockets open in the memory image:

1. Process ID 4 (System) has an open TCP connection to 192.168.0.176 on port 139.
2. Process ID 880 (svchost.exe) has an open TCP connection to 0.0.0.0 on port 1185.
3. Process ID 1244 (svchost.exe) has open TCP connections to 192.168.0.1 on port 30379 and 30380.
4. Process ID 888 (firefox.exe) has open TCP connections to 192.168.0.176 on port 1176 and 1172.
5. Process ID 1752 (AcroRd32.exe) has an open TCP connection to 212.150.164.203 on port 1178.

These connections could indicate potential malicious activities, especially if they are communicating with external or unusual IP addresses. Further analysis and investigation are recommended to determine the nature and impact of these connections on the system.
